00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:01,440
which are how systems move.

296
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:02,580
Well,

297
00:11:02,580 --> 00:11:03,980
I'm not quite ready for that yet,

298
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:05,060
because I do want to...

299
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:07,260
I do want to review a little bit,

300
00:11:07,260 --> 00:11:08,660
and to do

301
00:11:08,660 --> 00:11:12,040
a little bit of mathematical formalism,

302
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,800
which we haven't discussed yet.

303
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:18,160
First of all,

304
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:21,240
let me remind you what you do with states,

305
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,280
when you have them.

306
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,320
States are vectors.

307
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,820
They're the bra vectors and ket vectors.

308
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:29,940
And there are two interesting,

309
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:33,060
physically interesting things that you can do.

310
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:35,920
Let us suppose you know the state of a system,

311
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:38,580
and you're interested in some observable.

312
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,000
Well,

313
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,220
one thing you can do is to

314
00:11:42,220 --> 00:11:44,440
compute the average value of the observable,

315
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:48,140
the thing that most physicists call the expectation value.

316
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:51,880
Let's call the observable again just k for...

317
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:52,180
well,

318
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:52,260
k for...

319
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:52,360
Well,

320
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,640
yeah,

321
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:54,440
k is fine.

322
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:56,900
Sometimes I remember to put the

323
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:58,280
little hat on top of it,

324
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,140
sometimes I don't.

325
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:03,840
The average of it is just a sandwich,

326
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:04,260
k,

327
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:07,260
between the state,

328
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,400
the ket version of the state,

329
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,320
and the bra version of the state.

330
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:12,720
That's the average.

331
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,530
And it would be something which would be

332
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:20,660
useful if you were going to measure k,

333
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,200
if you were going to prepare the system,

334
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,940
and the same state over and over again,

335
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,760
and many,

336
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:26,860
many measurements of k,

337
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,580
and take the average.

338
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,480
It would be a useful thing to do.

339
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:32,280
And it's a physically interesting quantity.

340
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,060
Another thing is,

341
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:35,360
supposing we have two states.

342
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:38,540
Supposing we have a and b.

343
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,300
And as it happens,

344
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:43,840
a and b are eigenvectors of two different observables.

345
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:47,820
Let's say that a is an eigenvector of k,

346
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,360
with eigenvalue...

347
00:12:51,220 --> 00:12:52,940
Let's call it...

348
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:55,600
alpha...

349
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,560
times a.

350
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:03,260
And let's suppose that b happens to

351
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:05,960
be an eigenvector of a totally different observable,

352
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,960
l,

353
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:13,400
which happens to have eigenvalue beta times b.

354
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:17,360
There are two eigenvectors,

355
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,600
but of different operators.

356
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:22,390
Then the interesting quantity that

357
00:13:22,390 --> 00:13:24,420
we've discussed over and over again,

358
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,880
although I may not have spelled

359
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:27,200
it out in quite this detail,

360
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:28,500
is we could ask,

361
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:33,200
what's the probability that if we prepare a system

362
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:38,700
with a definite value of the observable k,

363
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:40,360
namely alpha,

364
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,360
we do something to the system

365
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:45,280
so as to make k definite,

366
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,480
and namely with a value of alpha,

367
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:49,040
then what's the probability that if

368
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,340
we then do something to the system,

369
00:13:50,340 --> 00:13:51,200
we then measure l,

370
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:53,200
that we get beta?

371
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:58,040
What's the probability that if we measure l,

372
00:13:59,620 --> 00:14:01,180
we get the answer beta,

373
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:03,660
given that we prepare the system

374
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:06,020
with a definite value of k,

375
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,920
namely equal to alpha?

376
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:10,360
The answer is...

377
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:15,460
the inner product of a with b...

378
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:17,740
squared.

379
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,200
Or another way to write it,

380
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:23,700
is times its complex conjugate,

381
00:14:25,199 --> 00:14:27,360
which we can write as b times a.

382
00:14:30,580 --> 00:14:31,520
That's equal...

383
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,160
that's equal to two things,

384
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:33,580
in fact.

385
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,780
We can call it the probability a,

386
00:14:35,780 --> 00:14:35,960
b.

387
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,680
It's the probability,

388
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:38,720
again,

389
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:42,020
that if we prepare the state with alpha,

390
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:44,260
and then measure l,

391
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:45,180
that we get beta,

392
00:14:45,340 --> 00:14:47,010
but it also happens to be the

393
00:14:47,010 --> 00:14:48,680
probability that if we prepare the state

394
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,480
with l equals beta,

395
00:14:50,940 --> 00:14:52,200
and then measure k,

396
00:14:52,620 --> 00:14:53,580
that we get alpha.

397
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:54,660
Was that clear?

398
00:14:57,740 --> 00:14:58,140
Well,

399
00:14:58,140 --> 00:14:58,920
it hardly matters,

400
00:14:58,940 --> 00:14:59,940
since you get the same answer.

401
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:05,100
Oh,

402
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:05,940
did I write it wrong?

403
00:15:06,020 --> 00:15:06,320
You're right,

404
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:06,640
I did.

405
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:14,600
Right.

406
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:17,540
This one is the complex conjugate of this.

407
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:18,360
Now,

408
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:18,660
this is the complex conjugate of this.

409
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,100
And these are the two kinds of questions

410
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:21,560
that you ask in quantum mechanics.

411
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:24,900
Average values for an ensemble of many experiments,

412
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:25,940
and,

413
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:26,420
again,

414
00:15:26,420 --> 00:15:27,180
probabilities,

415
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:27,640
which,

416
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:27,880
again,

417
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:30,500
only make sense for many repeated experiments.

418
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,300
Both of these have the feature

419
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:37,880
that the answers are insensitive

420
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:40,540
to a certain operation that you can do

421
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:42,420
on any one of the vectors in the space.

422
00:15:42,820 --> 00:15:44,720
And the operation is called

423
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,620
multiplying the vector by a phase.

424
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:47,380
Oh,

425
00:15:47,380 --> 00:15:48,180
before I go on,

426
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:49,460
let me just remind you of one thing,

427
00:15:50,110 --> 00:15:53,740
that physical state vectors always should be normalized

428
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:57,060
to make the total probability equal to one.

429
00:15:58,520 --> 00:15:59,500
That's one rule.

430
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:02,260
So we can think of

431
00:16:02,260 --> 00:16:03,860
physical state vectors as unit vectors.

432
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:05,860
Simply,

433
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:08,080
that's the statement that the sums of the squares

434
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,760
of the coefficients,

435
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:13,020
when you expand the state in a basis,

436
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:14,760
those should add up to one.

437
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,020
All right.

438
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:18,160
But let's discuss a little bit

439
00:16:18,180 --> 00:16:19,640
what's another operation that you can do.

440
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,060
You can take a state,

441
00:16:21,060 --> 00:16:22,140
or the whole state,

442
00:16:22,340 --> 00:16:23,780
not a piece of it

443
00:16:23,780 --> 00:16:25,220
individually when you add up pieces,

444
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,380
but the whole state,

445
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:27,140
the whole vector,

446
00:16:27,619 --> 00:16:30,040
and you can multiply it by a phase.

447
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:31,720
And I'm going to explain

448
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:33,140
what that means in a moment.

449
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:35,180
But the point is,

450
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:37,120
it doesn't make any difference whatever

451
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:39,240
to the physical properties of the state.

452
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:39,520
All right.

453
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,220
So first of all,

454
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:41,080
what does a phase mean?

455
00:16:41,580 --> 00:16:43,200
A phase is a complex number.

456
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,740
Let's just remember very quickly,

457
00:16:44,820 --> 00:16:48,160
for those who haven't read the book,

458
00:16:48,180 --> 00:16:50,900
I've been using complex numbers for the last 50 years.

459
00:16:51,020 --> 00:16:53,580
A complex number is an x and a y

460
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:55,520
with an x equal to iy.

461
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,390
It also can be represented

462
00:16:58,390 --> 00:16:59,880
as an r and a theta.

463
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:04,960
And it can be represented in the form

464
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:09,180
x and x plus iy.

465
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,020
x plus iy,

466
00:17:12,020 --> 00:17:14,280
that's the complex number z.

467
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,160
It can also be represented as a complex number z.

468
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:21,460
It can be written in the form r cosine theta,

469
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:26,560
that's x plus ir sine theta,

470
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:28,099
that's y.

471
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:33,480
And another way of expressing it,

472
00:17:34,419 --> 00:17:36,380
which is just more or less notation,

473
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,110
is to write it as r

474
00:17:38,110 --> 00:17:39,520
times e to the i theta.

475
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:41,670
e to the i theta

476
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:42,980
is just another way of writing

477
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:45,140
cosine theta plus i sine theta.

478
00:17:45,980 --> 00:17:47,120
Very quickly,

479
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:50,300
when you multiply two complex numbers,

480
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:53,480
you multiply their r's

481
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:55,740
and you add their angles.

482
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:58,520
So if we had two complex numbers,

483
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,930
let's call one of them

484
00:17:59,930 --> 00:18:01,160
r e to the i theta,

485
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:03,260
the other one let's call it,

486
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:05,620
what's another letter that's near r?

487
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:06,540
r two.

488
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:09,280
No.

489
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,340
Yes.

490
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,800
r one and theta one,

491
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:13,420
sorry,

492
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:14,020
theta one.

493
00:18:14,780 --> 00:18:17,160
And another complex number r two,

494
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:19,040
e to the i theta two.

495
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:24,080
Adding them is easy in this form.

496
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:25,420
We just add the components.

497
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,780
Multiplying them is easy in this form.

498
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:30,820
When you multiply two complex numbers,

499
00:18:31,140 --> 00:18:35,060
the result is r one r two.

500
00:18:35,460 --> 00:18:37,960
You multiply the lengths,

501
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:41,300
and then you add the angles,

502
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:44,100
e to the i theta one plus theta two.

503
00:18:48,899 --> 00:18:50,200
One more point.

504
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:52,920
The notion of complex conjugate,

505
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:57,180
the complex conjugate of a complex number

506
00:18:57,820 --> 00:19:00,100
is just the corresponding complex number

507
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:01,240
in the lower half plane,

508
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,720
which has exactly the same form r,

509
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,380
except instead of e to the i theta,

510
00:19:07,740 --> 00:19:10,020
it has e to the minus i theta.

511
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:13,540
So whatever z is,

512
00:19:13,740 --> 00:19:15,340
r e to the i theta,

513
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:21,500
z star is r e to the minus i theta.

514
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,380
Now in particular,

515
00:19:24,380 --> 00:19:25,420
there are special numbers,

516
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:27,460
which are called just pure phases,

517
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:29,400
special complex numbers,

518
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:32,000
for which r is equal to one.

519
00:19:32,820 --> 00:19:36,720
They are the numbers which lie on the unit circle.

520
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:40,000
The numbers which lie on the unit circle

521
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:44,040
in other words,

522
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,800
for which r is equal to one,

523
00:19:46,980 --> 00:19:50,000
and theta can vary around from zero to two pi,

524
00:19:50,780 --> 00:19:52,920
those numbers are called phases.

525
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,140
Well actually,

526
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:54,500
usually,

527
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,160
the language is a little bit ambiguous.

528
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:59,120
Sometimes the angle is called the phase,

529
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:01,360
and sometimes any number,

530
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,770
which is of the form e

531
00:20:02,770 --> 00:20:04,100
to the i times an angle,

532
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:05,060
is called a phase.

533
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,380
All right.

534
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:08,080
So e to the i,

535
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:08,400
e to the i,

536
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:11,760
theta is a special kind of number,

537
00:20:12,580 --> 00:20:14,040
which I will call a phase,

538
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:16,320
even though sometimes the phase

539
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:18,340
is reserved for the angle there.

540
00:20:19,220 --> 00:20:20,600
And it has the property

541
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:23,760
that when you multiply it by its complex conjugate,

542
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:25,360
let's call this z,

543
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:29,500
if we multiply z times z star,

544
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:32,700
and if z is a pure phase,

545
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:34,940
then the result is just one.

546
00:20:35,180 --> 00:20:35,980
Why is that?

547
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:38,320
Because it's e to the i theta,

548
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,940
times e to the minus i theta.

549
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:45,320
And when you multiply complex numbers,

550
00:20:45,540 --> 00:20:47,260
you just add the phases,

551
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:50,380
and e to the zero is just one.

552
00:20:51,220 --> 00:20:51,860
All right.

553
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,360
So this is a special class of numbers,

554
00:20:53,380 --> 00:20:56,980
which are characterized by z times z star equal one.

555
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:58,620
Good.

556
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:02,440
Now what does that have to do with these vectors?

557
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:05,240
Formally,

558
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:07,660
or just mathematically,

559
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,940
we distinguish two vectors.

560
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,660
Let's call one of them a,

561
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:16,490
and let's call the other e

562
00:21:16,490 --> 00:21:19,060
to the i theta times a,

563
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,840
where theta is any angle,

564
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:21,660
a number.

565
00:21:22,120 --> 00:21:23,040
All right.

566
00:21:23,220 --> 00:21:24,420
This is a vector.

567
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:26,400
This is a number times a vector.

568
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,020
Formally speaking,

569
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:29,880
they're two different vectors,

570
00:21:29,980 --> 00:21:33,660
just as a vector and twice the vector

571
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:35,160
are two different vectors.

572
00:21:36,340 --> 00:21:38,060
So mathematically speaking,

573
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:40,940
this vector is not equal to this vector.

574
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,430
But all of the physical

575
00:21:44,430 --> 00:21:46,420
properties of these two are identical.

576
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:49,100
How to see that?

577
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,280
Let's go back to the various things

578
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:54,560
that we might do with

579
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:57,720
or the various physical questions we might ask.

580
00:21:58,020 --> 00:21:59,020
For example,

581
00:21:59,180 --> 00:22:01,240
supposing we took psi here.

582
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:04,140
Let's take the case of the expectation value

583
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:07,020
